Paper: hep-th/0110102

Date: 2001-10-11

Title: On Linearization of N=1 Nonlinear Supersymmetry

Authors: K. Shima, Y. Tanii and M. Tsuda

Comments: 10 pages, LaTeX, references added and minor corrections

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B525 (2002) 183-188

The N=1 Volkov-Akulov model of nonlinear supersymmetry is explicitly relatedto a vector supermultiplet model with a Fayet-Iliopoulos D term of linearsupersymmetry. The physical significance of the results is discussed briefly.